## Lookup argument

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `key` | Required. The registry setting key to read. Must exist in the backend registry — an unknown key returns an error. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `key` | The setting key. |
| `value` | Current value as JSON (sensitive). Decode with `jsondecode()`. **Masked as `****` for secret keys.** |
| `description` | Human-readable description from the registry. |
| `is_secret` | Whether the value is a secret (masked in responses). |
| `default` | Registry default value as JSON. Masked as `****` for non-empty secret keys. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

For the complete list of valid `key` values — with each key's value type, range
or enum constraints, default, and whether it is secret — see the
[`mistershell_setting` resource](../resources/setting.md) page.
